def: Pertaining to, or inhabiting, a fen; abounding in fens; swampy;boggy. "Fenny snake." Shak.
More lofty; still higher; ever upward.

An alkaloid distinct from picrotoxin and obtained from thecocculus indicus (the fruit of Anamirta Cocculus, formerlyMenispermum Cocculus) as a white, crystalline, tasteless powder; --called also menispermina.
An instrument having two handles and two grasping jaws workingon a pivot; -- used for griping things to be held fast, drawingnails, etc.
The signs, abbreviations, letters, or characters standing forwords, shorthand, etc., in ancient manuscripts, or on coins, medals,etc. W. Savage.
the yarn or thread of any stuff of which the strands of a ropeare made.
